subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.
Male. Body slender, from moderately (
Fig. 8D, E
) to very shiny (
Fig. 8A
), legs and antennae slen- der, long. Head with moderately coarse, sparse puncturation (puncture diameter subequal to interpuncture distance). Head ventrally with simple (not impressed) longitudinal furrow beyond prementum. Pronotum moderately convex. Lateral margins of pronotum evenly rounded, emarginated or rarely straight at basal quarter; anterior angles not protruding or rarely slightly protruding; base bisinuate, posterior angles rectangular, weakly protruding. Pronotum punctured by uniform fine and sparse round punctures. Prosternal process comparatively wide, rounded at apex. Elytra widest at middle, with lateral margins less rounded. Strial punctures moderate in size or large, densely spaced (35–40 punctures in one row), round, not impressed or slightly impressed. Interstriae with fine and sparse distinctly visible puncturation. Protibiae narrow, with deep and wide notches on inner side and protruding, weakly obtuse tooth before the indentation; protibia widest at level of tooth. Mesotibiae usually straight, sometimes weakly bent. Mesotarsomeres 1–4 not widened, tarsomere 2 with reduced hair brush on sole, very rarely mesotarsomere 3 also with very small reduced hair tuft.
